excerpt: Simple restaurant specializing in local classics such as kalua pork, lomi salmon, and ribs.
detail_description: Helena's Hawaiian Food is a beloved restaurant in Honolulu, serving up traditional Hawaiian dishes since 1946. The casual setting and simple menu allow the focus to be on the delicious food, including kalua pork, lomi salmon, pipikaula (quick ribs), and squid luau. This family-run gem has received accolades such as the James Beard Americas Classics award in 2000 for its authentic regional cuisine.
name: Helena's Hawaiian Food
address: 1240 N School St, Honolulu, HI 96817, USA

excerpt: Featuring globally accented, modern Vietnamese cooking in a lively setting with communal tables.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant heart of Honolulu's Chinatown, The Pig and The Lady is a must-visit for anyone craving modern Vietnamese cuisine with a twist. This family-run gem offers an exciting menu that changes regularly, showcasing inventive dishes that are rich in flavor and creativity. One standout item is their famous pho French dip sandwich, which has garnered rave reviews for its unique combination of braised brisket and Thai basil chimichurri, served alongside a comforting bowl of pho broth perfect for dipping.
name: The Pig and The Lady
address: 83 N King St, Honolulu, HI 96817, USA

excerpt: Popular option known for its beachfront location, surf 'n' turf, tiki vibe & umbrella drinks.
detail_description: Duke's Waikiki is a popular beachfront restaurant with a tiki vibe and lively atmosphere, located facing Waikiki's famous Canoes surf break. Named after Duke Kahanamoku, the father of modern surfing, the casual spot offers a variety of appetizers, a large salad bar, and crowd-pleasing entrees such as fish and prime rib. The venue also features memorabilia honoring Duke Kahanamoku and serves the famous Hula Pie dessert.
name: Duke's Waikiki

excerpt: Elevated Hawaiian & New American menus, with imaginative drinks, served in refined surrounds.
detail_description: Senia is a highly acclaimed restaurant in Honolulu, offering both Hawaiian and New American cuisine in an elegant setting. The establishment was founded by Chris Kajioka and Anthony Rush, former Per Se alums, who have created a unique dining experience. Guests can choose from a diverse menu featuring modern American small plates, pastas, and large-format platters in the main dining area or opt for the luxurious $185-per-person tasting menu at the 12-seat chef's counter.
name: Senia
address: 75 N King St, Honolulu, HI 96817, USA

excerpt: Local fixture since 1952 for malasadas (Portuguese donuts), breads, pastries & other sweets.
detail_description: Leonard's Bakery has been a beloved local establishment since 1952, renowned for its malasadas, Portuguese donuts that are slightly crispier and chewier than traditional doughnuts. The bakery's influence extends beyond Hawaii, with franchises in Japan. Visitors can savor these delectable treats at scenic locations on the island during guided tours or simply stop by the bakery to indulge in a variety of flavors, from classic custard-filled to tropical-inspired options.
name: Leonard's Bakery

excerpt: Celeb chef Lee Anne Wong runs this brunch stop for breakfast udon, congee & other Pan-Asian eats.
detail_description: Koko Head Cafe, located in Kaimuki, Honolulu, is a popular brunch spot run by celebrity chef Lee Anne Wong. The menu offers a fusion of Asian and Hawaiian flavors with creative dishes like breakfast udon and congee. One of the highlights is the Koko Moco, featuring a medium-rare beef patty on crispy garlic rice with mushroom gravy, a sunny side egg, and kimchi tempura.
name: Koko Head Cafe

excerpt: Relaxed beachside venue serving pupu, fish tacos & tropical drinks, plus weekend brunch.
detail_description: Nestled right by the shimmering shores of Waikiki Beach, Hula Grill Waikiki is a delightful plantation-style eatery that offers an inviting atmosphere for both locals and visitors. Situated on the second floor of the Outrigger Waikiki Hotel, this charming venue provides stunning views of Diamond Head and breathtaking sunsets. Whether you're in the mood for a leisurely breakfast featuring fluffy pineapple pancakes or a sumptuous dinner showcasing fresh regional seafood and prime steaks, Hula Grill has something to satisfy every palate.
name: Hula Grill Waikiki

excerpt: Seafood specials, prime rib & jumbo mai tais in a polished, breezy space where sandy feet are okay.
detail_description: Nestled at the base of the Ko'olau Mountains, Haleiwa Joe's Haiku Gardens offers a serene and picturesque setting for both weddings and dining. The venue features beautiful botanical gardens and an open-air Tahitian Chapel, providing dreamy backdrops for intimate ceremonies. Couples can choose from various wedding packages, ranging from minimalist options to comprehensive packages with added services like a ceremony musician and wedding planner.
name: Haleiwa Joe's Haiku Gardens

excerpt: Upscale, ocean-front Royal Hawaiian spot for local seafood, with Spanish-Moorish decor & cabanas.
detail_description: Azure is an upscale, ocean-front restaurant located at the Royal Hawaiian with Spanish-Moorish decor and cabanas. The restaurant offers stunning views of Diamond Head and Waikiki Beach, creating a calm island atmosphere. It serves breakfast, lunch, and dinner with a sophisticated evening ambiance. The menu features local seafood, meat, produce, and a chef's multicourse tasting option. Desserts like Russian honey cake and Baked Alaska are also available.
name: Azure

excerpt: Shop selling cream pies, cakes, breads & pastries, plus hot sandwiches & plate lunches.
detail_description: Teds Bakery is a beloved establishment on Oahu's North Shore, offering a wide array of delectable treats such as cream pies, cakes, breads, and pastries. Renowned for its legendary chocolate haupia cream pie, this casual eatery provides an authentic Hawaiian dining experience that has captured the hearts of families and visitors alike. Situated at Sunset Beach with ample outdoor seating, patrons can savor their delicious offerings while enjoying the refreshing breeze from the famous Northern Coast.
name: Ted's Bakery

excerpt: Bakery & diner since 1950, popular for its breakfasts, comfort food & coco puffs.
detail_description: Liliha Bakery, a beloved establishment since 1950, is renowned for its delectable breakfast offerings and comforting dishes. The bakery prides itself on using locally sourced ingredients and crafting all their baked goods from scratch. With its original location on Honolulu's N. Kuakini St., the bakery has expanded to two additional locations due to its immense popularity.
name: Liliha Bakery
address: 515 N Kuakini St, Honolulu, HI 96817, USA

excerpt: Quaint, pint-sized grocery store is a local draw for its counter-serve shave ice & ice cream.
detail_description: Waiola Shave Ice is a popular local spot in Honolulu known for its counter-serve shave ice and ice cream. The quaint grocery store offers a variety of shave ice flavors, including classic options and new creations. One must-try is the Azuki Bowl, featuring shave ice topped with azuki beans, condensed milk, and mochi balls. This small snack shop off the side of the road exudes a definite local vibe and is frequented by both locals and visitors alike.
name: Waiola Shave Ice

excerpt: Locals flock to this no-frills eatery for the variety of ahi poke & a chill, laid-back atmosphere.
detail_description: Ono Seafood is a popular no-frills eatery known for its variety of ahi poke and laid-back atmosphere. The owner, Judy Samuka, is renowned for making some of the best poke on the island. The menu offers classic local favorites with made-to-order poke featuring buttery soft ahi and tender tako flavored with various options like shoyu, miso, sea salt, or wasabi.
name: Ono Seafood

excerpt: Cheery spot for creative breakfast & lunch made using local ingredients, plus cocktails.
detail_description: Over Easy is a vibrant eatery that serves up creative breakfast and lunch dishes made with locally sourced ingredients, along with a selection of cocktails. Their signature dish features two soft-cooked eggs, spinach, microgreens, candied bacon for a delightful salty-sweet crunch, tomato jam, yogurt, and tangy house-made sourdough toast. The menu offers fresh and healthy options while also indulging in treats like bacon and toast.
name: Over Easy

excerpt: Chef Roy Yamaguchi's Hawaiian cooking using locally sourced ingredients at the Turtle Bay Resort.
detail_description: Beach House by Roy Yamaguchi is a Hawaiian restaurant located at the Turtle Bay Resort, offering Euro-Asian cuisine with locally sourced ingredients. The restaurant boasts stunning views of Kuilima Cove and the ocean, creating a perfect ambiance for a casual dining experience. Guests can enjoy dishes like sashimi plate, soft shell crab bun, miso cod, and fork-tender short rib with honey mustard sauce while taking in the breathtaking ocean views.
name: Beach House by Roy Yamaguchi

excerpt: Chic hotel bar & eatery for modern takes on traditional Hawaiian seafood, plus tropical cocktails.
detail_description: Mina's Fish House, located at the Four Seasons Resort Oahu at Ko Olina, offers a modern twist on traditional Hawaiian seafood and tropical cocktails. Designed by James Beard Award winner Michael Mina, the restaurant features a line-to-table menu that celebrates local catch and provides panoramic views from both indoor and lanai oceanfront tables.
name: Mina's Fish House

excerpt: Seaside eatery doling out creative Pacific Rim fare & brunch at the New Otani Kaimana Beach Hotel.
detail_description: Hau Tree is a beachfront restaurant and bar located at the New Otani Kaimana Beach Hotel, offering creative Pacific Rim cuisine and a relaxing atmosphere. The eatery underwent a revamp in 2021 along with the hotel, featuring a casual-luxury aesthetic with teak and rope-trimmed chairs, coastal palette, woven light fixtures, and custom accent tiles.
name: Hau Tree
address: Lobby floor of the Kaimana Beach Hotel, 2863 Kalākaua Ave, Honolulu, HI 96815, USA

excerpt: Fans line up for shave ice in exotic flavors & combos, plus ice cream, at this local institution.
detail_description: Matsumoto Shave Ice is a must-visit local institution on the North Shore, known for its exotic flavors and creative combinations. Visitors often line up to savor the legendary shave ice, which can be found in Haleiwa. The affordable prices and refreshing taste make it a popular choice among tourists exploring the area's attractions like Hukilau Market and Polynesian Cultural Centre.
name: Matsumoto Shave Ice

excerpt: Live Hawaiian dancing & music under the stars paired with inventive island cocktails & pupus.
detail_description: House Without A Key is a popular indoor/outdoor restaurant in Waikiki known for its inventive island cocktails, locally sourced menu items, and live Hawaiian entertainment. Guests can enjoy sunset cocktails and appetizers while listening to live Hawaiian music under the stars by the sea. The venue offers a romantic and nostalgic atmosphere with a lovely hula dancer swaying to the riffs of Hawaiian steel-pedal guitar against the backdrop of a glowing sunset and ocean.
name: House Without A Key

excerpt: Large waterside hub showcasing locally sourced seafood & dishes mixing French & Hawaiian styles.
detail_description: Nico's Pier 38 is a popular waterfront dining spot that offers a relaxed atmosphere while serving top-notch seafood dishes with a blend of French and Hawaiian influences. The open-air setting provides breathtaking views of the harbor, creating a special dining experience. The menu highlights local flavors and ingredients, with the furikake ahi being particularly renowned. As Honolulu's premier fish restaurant, Nico's sources its fresh fish directly from the local fleet and emphasizes locally grown produce.
name: Nico's Pier 38
address: 1129 N Nimitz Hwy, Honolulu, HI 96817, USA

excerpt: A stylish spot for artisan Kona coffee and b. patisserie baked goods.
detail_description: Kona Coffee Purveyors is a stylish destination that offers artisan Kona coffee and delectable baked goods from b. patisserie. Greenwell Farms, situated in the heart of Hawaii's Kona Coffee Belt, has been a pioneer in the industry since its first award at the Vienna Worlds Expo in 1873. The farm is committed to producing top-quality 100% Kona Coffee with various flavor profiles, adhering to world gourmet standards. Meanwhile, b.
name: Kona Coffee Purveyors
address: Kuhio Mall Entrance, 2330 Kalākaua Ave, Honolulu, HI 96815, USA

excerpt: Guests order at the counter at this casual Japanese restaurant specializing in noodle soup.
detail_description: If you're on the hunt for a delightful dining experience in Hawaii, look no further than Marugame Udon. This casual Japanese eatery, with two locations in Honolulu, specializes in hand-crafted udon bowls and tempura. Staying true to traditional Japanese noodle-making techniques, Marugame Udon offers made-to-order noodles that you can watch being prepared right before your eyes.
name: Marugame Udon

excerpt: A trendy, colorful hotel bar turning out innovative Hawaiian plates and cocktails next to a pool.
detail_description: Mahina & Sun’s is a lively and trendy hotel bar located in The Surfjack Hotel & Swim Club, drawing both locals and tourists to its vibrant atmosphere. The bar boasts a cool, midcentury aesthetic with nods to 1960s Hawaiian surf culture, featuring custom work by local artisans. The menu offers innovative Hawaiian plates and craft cocktails, including the popular Lavender Rub and daily Market Special.
name: Mahina & Sun’s

excerpt: Iconic counter-serve spot for Hawaiian plate lunches features BBQ, mahi mahi, chili dogs & more.
detail_description: Rainbow Drive-In is a legendary Hawaiian spot known for its counter-serve style and delicious local food. Since 1961, it has been serving up iconic dishes like BBQ beef plate, Loco Moco plate, Rainbow Royal Burger, BBQ Ahi plate, and more. Despite its humble beginnings as a small eatery offering affordable meals, it has gained recognition from Honolulu Star Advertiser and Honolulu Magazine.
name: Rainbow Drive-In

excerpt: Chic, glass-walled dining room & terrace with bay views, serving creative meat & seafood dishes.
detail_description: 53 By The Sea is a stylish restaurant located in Honolulu, offering stunning bay views from its glass-walled dining room and terrace. Situated in a McVilla designed to attract Japanese wedding clientele, this establishment serves contemporary Continental cuisine with an emphasis on beautifully presented meat and seafood dishes. The crescent-shaped dining room provides breathtaking ocean views, making it an ideal spot for a romantic date night or upscale happy hour at the bar.
name: 53 By The Sea

excerpt: Simple & snug counter serve providing market-fresh takes on poke bowls inside Kekaulike Market.
detail_description: Maguro Brothers Hawaii Chinatown is a cozy counter-serve spot located in Kekaulike Market, offering market-fresh variations of poke bowls. The establishment is known for its emphasis on fresh fish and minimal seasonings, allowing the quality of the ingredients to shine. Run by experienced brothers from Tsukiji Fish Market in Japan, it's a seafood lover's paradise with offerings like Omakase 7 cuts of Sashimi and Maguro Kama Teriyaki.
name: Maguro Brothers Hawaii Chinatown
address: Maunakea Market Foodcourt, 1120 Maunakea St, Honolulu, HI 96817, USA

excerpt: Royal Hawaiian's beachfront bar is a festive, slick spot for umbrella cocktails, appetizers & music.
detail_description: Mai Tai Bar is a vibrant beachfront spot located at the Royal Hawaiian, offering an array of umbrella cocktails, appetizers, and live music. It's a festive and slick setting where you can enjoy the tropical vibes just steps away from the sand. The bar provides a perfect opportunity to savor fruity drinks while soaking in the stunning sunset views over the ocean.
name: Mai Tai Bar

excerpt: Farm-to-table eatery & bar for Hawaiian food, beer & cocktails, served in a casual space.
detail_description: Monkeypod Kitchen by Merriman is a farm-to-table restaurant and bar offering Hawaiian cuisine, beer, and cocktails in a laid-back setting. With locations in Maui and Oahu, it has become one of the most popular dining spots in Hawaii. The restaurant prioritizes local and organic ingredients, showcasing a seasonal menu with fresh produce. Chef Peter Merriman's culinary expertise shines through Hawaiian-inspired dishes like sweet bread buns for burgers and scratch-made pizza dough.
name: Monkeypod Kitchen by Merriman

excerpt: Classic steakhouse offering prime cuts, seafood & tableside service in an elegant setting.
detail_description: Hy's Steak House is a quintessential dining destination that has shaped the steakhouse experience in Canada and has become a beloved establishment in Hawaii over its impressive 45-year history. Nestled within an elegant setting adorned with aristocratic English-style library decor, this classic steakhouse specializes in USDA Prime Beef, expertly broiled over kiawe wood for an unforgettable flavor.
name: Hy's Steak House

excerpt: Laid-back steakhouse presents a surf 'n' turf menu & drinks in a tiki hut-style space.
detail_description: Buzz's Original Steak House is a laid-back restaurant located near Kailua Beach on Oahu's east side. The tiki hut-style space captures the spirit of old Hawaii, offering a surf 'n' turf menu and strong mai tais. With a rustic atmosphere and savory American favorites, it's an ideal spot for lunch or dinner. Customers praise the delicious scampi salad, Jack Daniels burgers, and Ahi wrap while enjoying the peaceful beachfront setting.
name: Buzz's Original Steak House

detail_description: Roy's Ko Olina is a top choice for those seeking Hawaiian-Asian cuisine in a stunning setting overlooking the golf course. The restaurant offers ever-changing menus, ensuring an exciting dining experience with entrees averaging around $50. Guests can indulge in fancy and romantic dinners, such as the smoky ahi poke and seafood treasure, or Uncle Roy's combo. The pineapple upside-down cake is a perfect way to end the meal.
name: Roy's Ko Olina

excerpt: Refined destination for upscale, chef-driven Japanese fare in a stylish setting with only 10 seats.
detail_description: Sushi Sho is an exclusive dining destination located within the luxurious Ritz-Carlton Waikiki Beach resort, offering an intimate setting with only 10 seats at the sushi counter and a separate private dining room. Helmed by chef-owner Keiji Nakazawa, a renowned sushi master, Sushi Sho presents a menu featuring over 40 varieties of fresh fish, blending modern and traditional styles with unique Hawaiian ingredients.
name: Sushi Sho

excerpt: Cozy restaurant specializing in Japanese breaded pork cutlets, plus seafood & poultry options.
detail_description: Ginza Bairin Tonkatsu is a cozy restaurant located in the heart of Waikiki, offering authentic Japanese cuisine with a focus on breaded pork cutlets. The star of the menu is Berkshire pork, creating crispy and juicy bites that are complemented by the specialty sauce created by founder Nobukatsu Shibuya. The restaurant also offers seafood and poultry options for those looking for variety.
name: Ginza Bairin Tonkatsu

excerpt: Store & cafe using the farm's produce for items like smoothies, liliko'i jelly & honey mango soap.
detail_description: Kahuku Farms is a family-run establishment that offers a unique farm-to-table experience. Situated on a 100-year-old family farm, the cafe and store utilize the farm's produce to create an array of delightful items such as smoothies, liliko'i jelly, and honey mango soap. Visitors can enjoy tours showcasing sustainable farming practices and indulge in mouth-watering treats like grilled banana bread and smoothie bowls made from tropical fruits grown on-site.
name: Kahuku Farms

excerpt: Cool, brick-walled hangout serving New American cuisine for lunch & dinner, plus cocktails & beer.
detail_description: Fête, located in Honolulu, is a popular restaurant celebrated for its farm-to-table approach and fusion of contemporary American dishes with Hawaiian flavors. The establishment has received the prestigious 2022 James Beard Award for Best Chef Northwest & Pacific. The menu features a variety of delectable options such as southern fried chicken, spaghetti carbonara, red snapper, vanilla ice cream, and raspberry sorbet.
name: Fête
address: 2 N Hotel St, Honolulu, HI 96817, USA

excerpt: The Sheraton's posh, beachside lounge known for unique cocktails, comfort food & coveted fire pits.
detail_description: RumFire, located at The Royal Hawaiian Hotel in Waikiki, is a luxurious beachside lounge offering stunning views of the water, Diamond Head, and sunset. During the day, guests can relax indoors or outdoors by the fire pits while sipping on cocktails featuring local Hawaiian flavors. The bar also hosts Spiked Afternoon Tea daily from 1-4pm. With a menu boasting around 80 rums organized by their countries of origin, RumFire is a haven for rum enthusiasts.
name: RumFire

excerpt: Famed chef Alan Wong presents his innovative, colorful Hawaiian fare in an upscale, 3rd-floor space.
detail_description: Alan Wong's Honolulu is a renowned restaurant located on the third floor of an office building in Honolulu. Despite not offering famous Hawaii views, the venue provides a sophisticated dining experience with its upscale and colorful Hawaiian fare. Chef Alan Wong, a James Beard Award winner and a prominent figure in the Hawaii Regional Cuisine movement, showcases his innovative dishes using local flavors and ingredients.
name: Alan Wong's Honolulu
address: 1857 S King St, Honolulu, HI 96826, USA

excerpt: Family-owned Thai kitchen with an upbeat,  convivial atmosphere & customizable fare.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Hawaii, Opal Thai is a charming family-owned restaurant that has transitioned from a beloved food truck to a cozy dining spot. Known for its vibrant and welcoming atmosphere, this eatery captivates locals and visitors alike with its commitment to fresh ingredients and authentic flavors. The experience at Opal Thai is unique; diners often find themselves guided by the owner, who crafts personalized recommendations based on individual tastes.
name: Opal Thai
address: 1030 Smith St Suite 6, Honolulu, HI 96817, USA

excerpt: Polished oceanfront hotel dating from 1901, offering a spa, refined dining & an outdoor pool.
detail_description: The Moana Surfrider, A Westin Resort & Spa, Waikiki Beach is a historic oceanfront hotel that has been welcoming guests since 1901. With its elegant blend of Victorian-era charm and modern amenities, this 793-room resort offers a variety of accommodations across three wings. Guests can enjoy refined dining options featuring locally-sourced ingredients and relax at the spa or outdoor pool.
name: Moana Surfrider, A Westin Resort & Spa, Waikiki Beach

excerpt: Local ingredients shine in Hawaiian-French fusion fare on an expertly prepared tasting menu.
detail_description: M by Jeremy Shigekane, formerly known as Chef Mavro, is a renowned Hawaiian-French fusion restaurant in Honolulu. The establishment has received numerous accolades, including the prestigious James Beard Award and AAA Five Diamond recognition. Chef Jeremy Shigekane's dedication to using local ingredients is evident in the expertly prepared tasting menus that showcase the marriage of food and wine.
name: M by Jeremy Shigekane (formerly Chef Mavro)
address: 1969 S King St, Honolulu, HI 96826, USA

excerpt: Humble, long-standing joint for traditional Hawaiian comfort foods & ice cream with outdoor seats.
detail_description: Nestled in the scenic east side of Oahu, Waiahole Poi Factory is a beloved spot that embodies the essence of traditional Hawaiian comfort food. This charming eatery, steeped in history, offers an array of mouthwatering dishes such as Laulau, Kalua Pig, and squid Luau. For those new to Hawaiian cuisine, the mixed plate is a perfect choice to sample various flavors.
name: Waiahole Poi Factory

excerpt: Quaint, casual stop for surf 'n' turf, pupu platters, colorful cocktails & a terrace with a view.
detail_description: Haleʻiwa Beach House is a popular seafood restaurant located on the North Shore of Oahu. The restaurant offers a variety of fresh seafood dishes, including shrimp and poke, as well as Hawaiian favorites like Kalua pork. Visitors can also enjoy modern twists on traditional dishes such as the Spicy Tuna Club and Beach House Loco Moco.
name: Haleʻiwa Beach House

excerpt: High-end chain serving notable chef Roy Yamaguchi's Hawaiian fusion fare in a contemporary setting.
detail_description: Roy's Waikiki is a high-end restaurant chain that offers a contemporary setting and serves Hawaiian fusion cuisine created by renowned chef Roy Yamaguchi. With over three decades of culinary excellence, the restaurant blends fresh local ingredients with bold flavors from Asia and the Pacific. The elegant dining room and exceptional service add sophistication to the dining experience while maintaining a tropical ambiance.
name: Roy's Waikiki

excerpt: Established, graffiti-decorated pit stop for a variety of shrimp plates & a garlic hot dog option.
detail_description: Giovanni's Shrimp Truck is a must-visit foodie destination on Oahu's North Shore. The graffiti-decorated pit stop offers a variety of shrimp plates and even a garlic hot dog option. One of the most popular menu items is the SCAMPI, known for its strong garlic flavor. While it may be touristy, Giovanni's lives up to the hype with its delicious offerings.
name: Giovanni's Shrimp Truck

excerpt: Cash-only coffeehouse offering up java, pastries, bagels & other light fare in a relaxed setting.
detail_description: Bogart's Café is a cash-only coffeehouse located in a strip mall near Diamond Head, offering a relaxed setting to enjoy java, pastries, bagels, and light fare. It's well-loved by locals and provides a great spot for breakfast or post-sunset dinner. The menu features items like seared scallops with cauliflower puree, pork chop with braised fennel, and the chef's signature cacio e pepe pasta.
name: Bogart's Café

excerpt: Easygoing eatery doling out locavore Hawaiian cuisine in breezy, surfer-themed environs.
detail_description: Goofy Cafe & Dine is a laid-back restaurant located within the Hilton Hawaiian Village Waikiki Beach Resort, offering a relaxed atmosphere with a surfer vibe. The cafe is known for its locavore Hawaiian cuisine, serving up farm-to-table breakfast options all day long. Despite having a small menu, the eatery prides itself on flavorful dishes made with fresh local ingredients. With friendly service and reasonable prices, it's a popular choice for breakfast in Waikiki.
name: GOOFY Cafe & Dine
address: 1831 Ala Moana Blvd #201, Honolulu, HI 96815, USA

excerpt: Elegant, classic French restaurant at Colony Surf offering fine dining with beach or city views.
detail_description: Michel's at the Colony Surf is an elegant and classic French restaurant located at the Colony Surf Hotel, offering fine dining with stunning beach or city views. The restaurant is known for its romantic ambiance and has been a favorite among both locals and visitors since 1962. The menu features classic French dishes such as Helix Escargots Bourgogne in herb-garlic sauce, Lobster Bisque, as well as Hawaiian-inspired entrees like Island-Style Steamed Fresh Fish.
name: Michel's at the Colony Surf

excerpt: Casual hangout with a buzzy atmosphere offering American comfort food standards.
detail_description: Nestled on a quaint, bustling lane near Ala Moana Center, Side Street Inn is the ultimate casual hangout for those craving American comfort food with a local twist. This beloved late-night sports bar has become a favorite among chefs and food enthusiasts alike, including renowned James Beard Award winner Alan Wong. With its unpretentious vibe and large shareable plates crafted by Chef Colin Nishida, diners can indulge in mouthwatering dishes like Hawaiian-style pulehu short ribs and crispy skin roast pork.
name: Side Street Inn

excerpt: Marina-based legend (set for the Hawaii Five-O TV show) with retro tiki decor & a Hawaiian menu.
detail_description: La Mariana Sailing Club is a legendary tiki bar located at the end of Sand Island Access Road in Honolulu. It offers a retro tiki decor and a Hawaiian menu, making visitors feel like they've stepped into an old Hawaii that no longer exists. The bar boasts furniture and decor from now-closed tiki legends, creating an authentic atmosphere.
name: La Mariana Sailing Club
address: 50 Sand Island Access Rd, Honolulu, HI 96819, USA

excerpt: Global fare & a popular Sunday brunch in a casually elegant space filled with the namesake flower.
detail_description: Orchids is a popular restaurant located in the Halekulani resort, offering a global menu and a renowned Sunday brunch. The elegant space is adorned with the namesake flower, creating a casually sophisticated atmosphere. With louvered walls open to refreshing breezes and colorful orchid displays, Orchids provides an inviting setting for diners.
name: Orchids
